 "framing": "The foundation-adapter rung: freeze SAM's 93 M-parameter ViT and tune ONLY its 37K normalization parameters plus a 388K decode head. That is under 0.5 percent of the network, yet it adapts a general segmenter to cracks. It shows the trade the rest of the ladder is measured against: near-frozen foundation weights vs a small task head, at a fraction of a full fine-tune's cost.",
 "limitation": "SAM was built for prompt-driven, object-scale segmentation; a 1-5 px crack is far from its training distribution, so the prompt-free head does the heavy lifting and the norm deltas only re-tune the statistics. The published 61.22 F1 is on OmniCrack30k, a larger and cleaner benchmark than these few examples; the per-sample numbers here are illustrative, not a benchmark result."
}